Ian Harris is a member of the Church of the Flying Spaghetti Monster . 
  His followers regard the pasta strainer as a religious garment . 
  He is challenging the DVLA over his right to wear the metal bowl in his licence photo . 
  Mr Harris says it is equivalent to Muslim women being pictured in hijabs . 
  He has been turned down once but has sent off a fresh photo in a second bid . 
  Other countries including Austria and the Czech Republic allow Pastafarians to wear a colander in their licence photos . 
 